properties.description: This North London walking tour will draw comparisons between the progress and demise of the postwar welfare state. Focussing on housing and healthcare, the tour will present prominent examples from the era in North London and discuss ways these are being adapted to meet contemporary challenges, such as the housing crisis and ongoing maintenance. The ambition of the tour is to reassess the value of postwar architecture today.
